author: app.com
title: World Series: Mets taking fans on storybook ride
text:
MORE What had been white noise grabbed my full attention last week when the caller on sports talk radio wondered if the Mets could be on the verge of a dynasty given their stockpile of young arms, as if four more wins was a given.
Ah, it’s nice to have the metropolitan area once again relevant come World Series time, the euphoria rendering irrelevant the fact that they haven’t won a championship in 29 years when weighted against a now grandiose vision of the future.
And that it’s the Mets still playing, with Game 1 set for Tuesday night in Kansas City, is a great thing for the game.
